    <div class="reveal">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">10 / Implementation</p>
    <h2>Technical Implementation</h2>

    <p>The technical foundations of AI search optimisation overlap with traditional technical SEO but include additional requirements specific to AI crawlers and LLM retrieval.</p>

    <h3>Schema Markup for AI</h3>

    <p>AI platforms parse JSON-LD schema more reliably than they parse unstructured text. A comprehensive schema implementation includes:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Organization schema</strong> with sameAs links to all official profiles, establishing your entity across platforms.</li>
      <li><strong>LocalBusiness schema</strong> with geographic coordinates, service area, and opening hours for local relevance.</li>
      <li><strong>Service schema</strong> with detailed descriptions of each service offering, linked to the provider entity.</li>
      <li><strong>FAQPage schema</strong> on every page with question-answer content, making Q&A pairs machine-readable.</li>
      <li><strong>Article schema</strong> on blog posts and thought leadership content, with author, date, and topic information.</li>
      <li><strong>BreadcrumbList schema</strong> on every page to communicate site hierarchy.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Content Structure for Extractability</h3>

    <p>Content that AI platforms can easily extract and cite follows specific structural patterns:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Inverted pyramid.</strong> Place the most important information first. Every section should open with a direct statement of fact or answer.</li>
      <li><strong>One topic per heading.</strong> Each H2 or H3 section should address a single, clearly defined topic. This allows AI systems to extract relevant passages without pulling in unrelated information.</li>
      <li><strong>Tables for comparative data.</strong> When presenting comparisons, pricing, or specifications, use HTML tables. AI platforms parse tables more accurately than prose descriptions of the same data.</li>
      <li><strong>Definition patterns.</strong> When defining terms or concepts, use a consistent pattern: "X is Y" in the opening sentence. This matches the extraction pattern most AI platforms use for definitional queries.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>FAQ Formatting for AI</h3>

    <p>FAQ sections serve dual purposes in AI search optimisation. For users, they provide quick answers to common questions. For AI platforms, they provide clearly structured question-answer pairs that can be directly cited. Each FAQ should use:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>The exact question phrasing a user would type into an AI assistant.</li>
      <li>A self-contained answer in the first sentence that makes sense without surrounding context.</li>
      <li>FAQPage schema markup linking the HTML content to machine-readable structured data.</li>
    </ul>

    </div>

